<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="258" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,1144,2071]" pageId="1" pageNumber="258">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,314,1144,1170]" pageId="1" pageNumber="258">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Akcicek" authorityYear="2022" box="[342,760,1144,1170]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Stachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="258" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="cretica" subSpecies="gulendamiana">
<emphasis box="[342,513,1144,1170]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="258">Stachys cretica</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[600,760,1144,1170]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="258">gulendamiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="K. H. Rechinger" authorityYear="1937" box="[911,1213,1144,1170]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Stachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="258" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="cretica" subSpecies="anatolica">
<emphasis box="[911,1017,1144,1170]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="258">S. cretica</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[1104,1213,1144,1170]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="258">anatolica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[1213,1217,1144,1170]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="258">,</emphasis>
but it differs mainly by its marine sandy habitat, indumentum adpressed white lanate- tomentose, flowering stems decumbent, basal leaves undulate, nutlets dull, greyish-brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
